<div type="commentary">
            <p>The charter is not intact. The single extant plate mentions a grant (<foreign>anumoda</foreign>) of or to a dam, as well as gifts of gold and textiles to various officials. The text is cut off at the start and end of the single engraved side of the plate, which is therefore believed to be neither the first nor last in the original set. The start of the text, suspected to contain the date and name of the issuing king, is lost. However, the names of officials mentions in the extant portion allow us to place this inscription in the reign of Balitung.</p>                
                       </div>
